PO.Data: Manufacturer or Government regulated directives to ensure the airworthiness of aircraft
Airworthiness Directives (AD) provide corrective actions that must be taken once or repetively to ensure the continued safe operation of the aircraft or component.

The applicability of an AD can be to a group of products, a single product (manufacturer/model) or specific components (an aircraft or part on an aircraft). The applicability will create maintenance corrective actions and tasks according to the compliance requirements for all affected components.

E.g., you cannot delete a Business Partner, if there are invoices for this partner record existing. You de-activate the Business Partner and prevent that this record is used for future entries.
